      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/10/the-satisfaction/#comment-42369"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-10-08T16:48:10-04:00">Wednesday, October 8, 2014 at 4:48 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I always sterilize the jars in the oven but I also boil the tops.  If you are able to use tongs, I find the jam jars will seal without the water bath as the jam is boiling hot, the jars are sterilized and so are the tops.  I plan to use your recipe for my next round of .strawberry jam, I have been a Certo girl all my life, as was my mother!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-42369' data-commentid="42369" data-postid="79" data-belowelement="comment-42369" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Carol Ann" aria-label='Reply to Carol Ann'>Reply</a>    </div>
