    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Also &#8211; regarding the foam at the beginning of the jam-making process &#8211; it will disappear (as much as it ever will &#8211; as much as if you&#39;d skimmed it off) during the cooking process.  I think it may be necessary when using commercial pectin because then there isn&#39;t time for it to incorporate back into the mass of jamminess.  By the time the jam is glossy and you start thinking about the saucers/spoons in the freezer, it&#39;ll be gone.  Like magic.  This is a discovery born out of pure laziness on my part&#8230;  Very exciting about sterilizing in the oven!</p>
    </div>

